ter the\ninterstellar icy grain mantles, releasing into the gas phase most of their P\ncontent, mainly in the form of PH$_3$, which is converted into atomic P, and\nthen ionised efficiently by cosmic rays, forming P$^+$. Further reactions with\nO$_2$ and OH produce PO$^{+}$. The cosmic-ray ionisation of PO might also\ncontribute significantly, which would explain the high $N$(PO$^{+}$)/$N$(PO)\nobserved. The relatively high gas-phase abundance of PO$^{+}$ with respect to\nother P-bearing species stresses the relevance of this species in the\ninterstellar chemistry of P.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Feb 2022 16:25:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-01"}
