$ = 200 GeV, respectively. These\ndatasets provide the most precise measurement of the Collins effect in 200 GeV\n$pp$ collisions to date, especially at the quark momentum fractions $0.1 \\le x\n\\le 0.4$. These proceedings present the preliminary results for Collins\nasymmetries of identified pions in jets in $pp$ collisions at $\\sqrt{s}$ = 200\nGeV and comparisons to theory predictions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Mar 2022 02:12:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-18"}
